- POT - Python Optimal Transport (https://pythonot.github.io/), MIT License
  Used: Sinkhorn-Knopp solver (ot.sinkhorn) as a runtime dependency.

== Design patterns referenced (no code vendored) ==

The following hinanohart projects (all MIT) informed the polyalign
design but are NOT vendored into the source tree or imported at runtime.
They are listed here for honest provenance only.

- hybridlens (https://github.com/hinanohart/hybridlens)
  Pattern: Hybrid (Mamba+Attention) SAE shape conventions.

- saelet (https://github.com/hinanohart/saelet)
  Pattern: cross-vendor SAE evaluation harness layout.

- foldgauge (https://github.com/hinanohart/foldgauge)
  Pattern: split conformal prediction reference.

- mosaicraft-active-vision (https://github.com/hinanohart/mosaicraft)
  Pattern: Sinkhorn-OT assignment use-case framing.

- weightlock (https://github.com/hinanohart/weightlock)
  Pattern: dependency license classification reference (not wired in
  v0.1.0a2 CI; v0.1.1 backlog).

